@node "WhatIsIt" "What is it?"
@next "Requirements"
@prev "Main"
  SerialKey is a little program I wrote a few years back, to allow me to enter
text on my CD32, using my A1200s keyboard. I'm currently tidying up and
releasing most of my programs, and this is amongst the first.
@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
@next "Usage"
@prev "WhatIsIt"
  SerialKey has been tested on an A1200 with 10MB of RAM, an 030 running
at 50mhz, and 540mb hard disk, and should run on any Amiga with Kickstart V36
or above, although I can't make any guarantees.
@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"
@next "Future"
@prev "Requirements"
  SerialKey is easy to run. Just connect two Amigas over their serial ports,
start a copy on each computer, and select the small SerialKey window that
opens, and type.
@endnode

@node "Future" "Future"
@next "AuthorInfo"
@prev "Usage"
  I'm planning on improving the serial and window handling code as I have
time. If someone wants to do this for me, the source is included, I'd
appreciate a copy of the new version. Newer versions will also be able to
be run from Workbench, and to have parameters like the serial device
changed.
@endnode

